# Leash — Data Model

## Entities

### Entity: Harness
The core Rust runtime. Monolithic for now; safety gates, pilot sessions, sim+physical drivers, telemetry broadcast.

```yaml
entity: Harness
type: entity
properties:
  role: {type: string, required: true, default: robot}
  profile: {type: enum, required: true, values: [sim, waveshare-ugv], default: sim}
  safety_gates: {type: string, required: true, description: deadman, estop, soft-odometry-limit, physical-actuation-gate}
  deadman_ms: {type: number, required: true, default: 400}
  soft_odometry_limit_m: {type: number, required: true, default: 0.0}
  allow_physical_actuation: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false}
  allow_untokened_drive: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true}
states: [planned, mapped, extracted, stabilized, released]
lifecycle: planned → mapped → extracted → stabilized → released
```

### Entity: ModuleGraph
Typed module runtime. Coordinator manages startup/shutdown order, health aggregation. Introspection exports for graph viz.

```yaml
entity: ModuleGraph
type: entity
properties:
  module_count: {type: number, required: true}
  stream_count: {type: number, required: true}
  isolation: {type: enum, required: true, values: [in_process, cross_process, network], default: in_process}
  coordinator: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: lifecycle + health aggregation (#17)}
  introspection: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: graph exports (#21)}
states: [planned, designed, implemented, tested, active]
lifecycle: planned → designed → implemented → tested → active
```

### Entity: Blueprints
Runnable catalog. Composition model for reusable stacks. `leash list` + `leash run <blueprint>`.

```yaml
entity: Blueprints
type: entity
properties:
  catalog: {type: string, required: true, description: sim-http, sim-mcp, compat-http, gated-hardware}
  composition: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: reusable stacks (#15)}
  built_in: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: discoverable run targets (#16)}
  versioned: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true}
states: [planned, cataloged, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → cataloged → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: Transport
Pub/sub abstraction. In-memory + local async backends. Stream backpressure, quality filtering, timestamp alignment.

```yaml
entity: Transport
type: entity
properties:
  backends: {type: string, required: true, description: in-memory, local-async-pubsub}
  backpressure: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: stream backpressure (#25)}
  quality_filtering: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: timestamp alignment helpers (#25)}
  default_backend: {type: enum, required: true, values: [in_memory, local_async], default: in_memory}
states: [planned, designed, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → designed → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: Telemetry
Live telemetry streaming via broadcast channel, WebSocket, SSE. TelemetryFrame with full sensor snapshot.

```yaml
entity: Telemetry
type: entity
properties:
  outputs: {type: string, required: true, description: broadcast, ws, sse, json_stream, mcp}
  websocket: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true, description: WS /ws/telemetry (#23)}
  sse: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: server-sent events (#23)}
  views: {type: string, required: true, description: graph, streams, spatial, command-center}
states: [planned, implemented, active]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → active
```

### Entity: Replay
Deterministic sensor record + replay. `leash record` + `leash replay`. Compact timestamped format.

```yaml
entity: Replay
type: entity
properties:
  buffer_format: {type: string, required: true, default: leash-replay-v1}
  determinism: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true}
  sensor_record: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: deterministic sensor replay (#24)}
states: [planned, implemented, verified]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → verified
```

### Entity: CLI
CLI + HTTP server. Subcommands: serve (mcp|http), health, stop. Daemon lifecycle pending (#18).

```yaml
entity: CLI
type: entity
properties:
  listen: {type: string, required: true, default: 127.0.0.1:8000}
  commands: {type: string, required: true, description: serve (mcp|http), health, stop}
  http_endpoints: {type: string, required: true, description: 16 REST + WS}
states: [planned, implemented, tested, released]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested → released
```

### Entity: MCPServer
MCP stdio server (rmcp). 7 tools. HTTP transport + CLI tool calls planned (#26).

```yaml
entity: MCPServer
type: entity
properties:
  tools: {type: string, required: true, description: health, capabilities, observe, invoke_capability, stop, estop, capture}
  transport: {type: enum, required: true, values: [stdio], description: HTTP planned (#26)}
  cli_tools: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: CLI tool calls (#26)}
states: [planned, implemented, tested, released]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested → released
```

### Entity: UGVAdapter
Waveshare Ubuntu UGV. Feature-gated behind `--features waveshare-ugv`. Serial JSON-line protocol.

```yaml
entity: UGVAdapter
type: entity
properties:
  target: {type: string, required: true, default: Waveshare Ubuntu UGV}
  feature_flag: {type: string, required: true, default: waveshare-ugv}
  serial_port: {type: string, required: true, default: /dev/ttyTHS1}
  serial_baud: {type: number, required: true, default: 115200}
  drive_invert: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false}
  drive_swap: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false}
states: [planned, implemented, feature_gated, documented]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → feature_gated → documented
```

### Entity: Bridge
Compatibility layer for existing robot bridge clients. Feature flag exists; shim code not yet written.

```yaml
entity: Bridge
type: entity
properties:
  clients: {type: string, required: true}
  shim_layer: {type: string, required: true}
states: [planned, mapped, documented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → mapped → documented → tested
```

### Entity: Safety
Runtime safety gates + smoke scripts + policy-gated capability invocation.

```yaml
entity: Safety
type: entity
properties:
  gates: {type: string, required: true, description: deadman, estop, soft-odometry-limit, physical-actuation-gate}
  smoke_scripts: {type: string, required: true, description: smoke-http.sh, smoke-mcp.py, smoke-physical-gate.sh}
  policy: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: safety classes + approval gates (#30)}
states: [planned, implemented, verified]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → verified
```

### Entity: ReleasePipeline
Packages for crates.io + GitHub binaries. Feature tier matrix planned (#42).

```yaml
entity: ReleasePipeline
type: entity
properties:
  targets: {type: string, required: true, description: crates.io, GitHub binaries}
  platforms: {type: string, required: true, description: linux-x86_64, macos-arm64}
states: [planned, configured, publishing]
lifecycle: planned → configured → publishing
```

### Entity: Bootstrap
Crate skeleton (leash-harness 0.1.0). MIT license. CI workflow exists, not yet green.

```yaml
entity: Bootstrap
type: entity
properties:
  license: {type: string, required: true, default: MIT}
  ci_platform: {type: string, required: true, default: GitHub Actions}
  crate_name: {type: string, required: true, default: leash-harness}
  features: {type: string, required: true, description: default=sim+http+mcp, waveshare-ugv, bridge-compat}
states: [planned, bootstrapped, ci_green]
lifecycle: planned → bootstrapped → ci_green
```

### Entity: Agent
Model-provider configuration + input channels. Deterministic fake model for CI. One-shot, interactive, web commands.

```yaml
entity: Agent
type: entity
properties:
  providers: {type: string, required: true, description: deterministic-test, openai-compatible-http, local-http}
  channels: {type: string, required: true, description: one-shot, interactive, web}
  ci_model: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: no-network fake model}
states: [planned, configured, active]
lifecycle: planned → configured → active
```

### Entity: CapabilityRegistry
Shared registry with schema + safety metadata. Routes HTTP, MCP, agent calls through one surface.

```yaml
entity: CapabilityRegistry
type: entity
properties:
  safety_classes: {type: string, required: true, description: observe-only, sim-control, physical-stop, physical-motion, physical-high-risk}
  policy_modes: {type: string, required: true, description: dry-run, require-token, require-approval, deny}
  schema_validation: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true}
states: [planned, implemented, active]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → active
```

### Entity: Perception
Detection/observation adapter. Spatial memory + object registry. File-backed store.

```yaml
entity: Perception
type: entity
properties:
  adapter: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: detection boundary (#37)}
  spatial_memory: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: tagged locations, objects, confidence (#36)}
  store: {type: enum, required: true, values: [file_backed], default: file_backed}
states: [planned, implemented, active]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → active
```

### Entity: Navigation
Occupancy-grid + costmap primitives. Sim waypoint router + local planner. Patrol + exploration.

```yaml
entity: Navigation
type: entity
properties:
  messages: {type: string, required: true, description: pose, twist, path, occupancy-grid, costmap, map-metadata}
  planner: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: sim waypoint router (#34)}
  patrol: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: coverage, frontier, random strategies (#35)}
  sim_only: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true}
states: [planned, designed, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → designed → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: CommandCenter
Localhost web dashboard. Health, telemetry, modules, capabilities, logs, estop/stop controls. Policy state visible.

```yaml
entity: CommandCenter
type: entity
properties:
  feature_flag: {type: string, required: true, default: dashboard}
  bind: {type: string, required: true, default: localhost}
  views: {type: string, required: true, description: health, telemetry, modules, capabilities, logs, policy, controls}
  capability_routing: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true, description: buttons call shared capability registry}
states: [planned, implemented, active]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → active
```

### Entity: DroneAdapter
MAVLink drone skeleton. Feature-gated. Sim/replay mode. Physical gate required for flight.

```yaml
entity: DroneAdapter
type: entity
properties:
  target: {type: string, required: true, default: MAVLink drone}
  feature_flag: {type: string, required: true, default: mavlink-drone}
  capabilities: {type: string, required: true, description: arm, disarm, takeoff, land, move-velocity, fly-to, observe, stop}
  sim_replay: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true}
states: [planned, implemented, feature_gated]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → feature_gated
```

### Entity: ManipulatorAdapter
Manipulator arm + teleop skeleton. Feature-gated.

```yaml
entity: ManipulatorAdapter
type: entity
properties:
  target: {type: string, required: true, default: robot arm manipulator}
  feature_flag: {type: string, required: true, default: manipulator}
  teleop: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true, description: teleop skeleton (#40)}
states: [planned, implemented, feature_gated]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → feature_gated
```

### Entity: HardwareMatrix
Adapter profile matrix + plugin boundary. Categories, capability sets, feature flags, required gates. Maturity levels.

```yaml
entity: HardwareMatrix
type: entity
properties:
  categories: {type: string, required: true, description: ground, aerial, manipulator}
  maturity_levels: {type: string, required: true, description: stable, beta, alpha, experimental}
  plugin_boundary: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: core vs feature/example crate separation}
states: [planned, defined, documented]
lifecycle: planned → defined → documented
```

### Entity: Daemon
Background run registry. XDG state directory. `leash run --daemon`, status, log, stop, restart.

```yaml
entity: Daemon
type: entity
properties:
  state_dir: {type: string, required: true, description: XDG-compatible}
  commands: {type: string, required: true, description: run --daemon, status, log, stop, restart}
  graceful_stop: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true}
states: [planned, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: Config
Resolved config precedence. `leash show-config`. Env vars + flags + config file merging.

```yaml
entity: Config
type: entity
properties:
  precedence: {type: string, required: true, description: flags > env > config-file > defaults}
  show_config: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true}
states: [planned, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: Logging
Structured JSONL logs. Lightweight resource monitor.

```yaml
entity: Logging
type: entity
properties:
  format: {type: enum, required: true, values: [jsonl], default: jsonl}
  resource_monitor: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false}
states: [planned, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: ReleaseMatrix
Feature tiers + dependency tiers + CI build matrix. Core, http, mcp, sim, dashboard, replay, visualization, hardware, perception, interop.

```yaml
entity: ReleaseMatrix
type: entity
properties:
  tiers: {type: string, required: true, description: core, http, mcp, sim, dashboard, replay, viz, hardware-adapters, perception, interop}
  default: {type: string, required: true, default: core+sim+http+mcp}
  ci_matrix: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false, description: core-only, default, all-features, mcp-only, hardware}
states: [planned, defined, verified]
lifecycle: planned → defined → verified
```

### Entity: CrossLanguage
Cross-language message schemas + client examples.

```yaml
entity: CrossLanguage
type: entity
properties:
  schemas: {type: string, required: true, description: JSON Schema, protobuf candidates}
  clients: {type: string, required: true, description: Python, JS/TS examples}
states: [planned, implemented, documented]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → documented
```

### Entity: SmokeSuite
Full no-hardware smoke suite. Blueprint run, daemon lifecycle, MCP HTTP, dashboard, replay, graph export, safety policy.

```yaml
entity: SmokeSuite
type: entity
properties:
  coverage: {type: string, required: true, description: blueprint-run, daemon-lifecycle, mcp-http, dashboard, replay, graph-export, safety-policy}
  no_hardware: {type: boolean, required: true, default: true}
  ci_integration: {type: boolean, required: true, default: false}
states: [planned, implemented, verified]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → verified
```

## Relationships

```yaml
relationships:
  - {from: Bootstrap, to: Harness, verb: provisions, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Harness, to: ModuleGraph, verb: contains, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Harness, to: CLI, verb: powers, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Harness, to: MCPServer, verb: powers, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Harness, to: Bridge, verb: exposes_through, cardinality: 1:many, required: true}
  - {from: Blueprints, to: ModuleGraph, verb: instantiates, cardinality: 1:many, required: true}
  - {from: Blueprints, to: Harness, verb: targets, cardinality: many:1, required: true}
  - {from: Transport, to: ModuleGraph, verb: connects, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Telemetry, to: ModuleGraph, verb: observes, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Telemetry, to: Harness, verb: introspects, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Replay, to: Blueprints, verb: exercises, cardinality: 1:many, required: true}
  - {from: Replay, to: Telemetry, verb: feeds, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: UGVAdapter, to: Harness, verb: adapts, cardinality: 1:1, required: false}
  - {from: Safety, to: Harness, verb: gates, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Safety, to: ModuleGraph, verb: gates, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Safety, to: UGVAdapter, verb: gates, cardinality: 1:1, required: false}
  - {from: Safety, to: Replay, verb: verifies, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: ReleasePipeline, to: Harness, verb: packages, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Bridge, to: CLI, verb: documents_for, cardinality: many:1, required: true}
  - {from: MCPServer, to: ModuleGraph, verb: exposes, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: MCPServer, to: Blueprints, verb: launches, cardinality: 1:many, required: true}
  - {from: Agent, to: Harness, verb: commands, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Agent, to: CapabilityRegistry, verb: routes_through, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: CapabilityRegistry, to: Harness, verb: gates, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: CapabilityRegistry, to: Safety, verb: enforces, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Perception, to: Harness, verb: observes, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Navigation, to: Harness, verb: controls, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Navigation, to: Perception, verb: depends_on, cardinality: 1:1, required: false}
  - {from: CommandCenter, to: Harness, verb: visualizes, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: CommandCenter, to: CapabilityRegistry, verb: routes_through, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: DroneAdapter, to: Harness, verb: adapts, cardinality: 1:1, required: false}
  - {from: ManipulatorAdapter, to: Harness, verb: adapts, cardinality: 1:1, required: false}
  - {from: HardwareMatrix, to: UGVAdapter, verb: classifies, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: HardwareMatrix, to: DroneAdapter, verb: classifies, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: HardwareMatrix, to: ManipulatorAdapter, verb: classifies, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Daemon, to: CLI, verb: extends, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Config, to: CLI, verb: feeds, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: Logging, to: Harness, verb: monitors, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: ReleaseMatrix, to: ReleasePipeline, verb: gates, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: CrossLanguage, to: ReleasePipeline, verb: documents, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: SmokeSuite, to: Safety, verb: proves, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
  - {from: SmokeSuite, to: Harness, verb: verifies, cardinality: 1:1, required: true}
```
